{"title_page": "Endless Night (2015 film)", "text_new": "{{short description|2015 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Endless Night\n| image          = Nadie quiere la noche.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Isabel Coixet]]\n| producer       = Jaume Roures\n| writer         = [[Miguel Barros]]\n| starring       = [[Juliette Binoche]]<br>[[Rinko Kikuchi]]<br>[[Gabriel Byrne]]\n| music          = [[Lucas Vidal]]\n| cinematography = [[Jean-Claude Larrieu (cinematographer)|Jean-Claude Larrieu]]\n| editing        = Elena Ruiz \n| production companies = Mer Film<br>New Art Productions<br>Noodles Production<br>One More Movie\n| distributor    = Filmax {{small|(Spain)}}, \n| released       = {{Film date|2015|2|5|[[65th Berlin International Film Festival|Berlin]]|2015|10|30|Spain|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 118 minutes\n| country        = Spain<br>France<br>Bulgaria\n| language       = English\n}}\n\n'''''Endless Night''''' ({{lang-es|'''Nadie quiere la noche'''}}) is a 2015 [[drama film]] directed by [[Isabel Coixet]]. It was selected to open the [[65th Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/isabel-coixets-nobody-wants-the-night-to-open-berlin-film-festival-1201396594/ | title=Berlin Film Festival to Open with Juliette Binoche Starrer \u2018Nobody Wants the Night\u2019 | work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] | publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] | date=9 January 2015 | accessdate=10 January 2015 | last=Barraclough | first=Leo}}</ref> The film is set in 1908 in [[Greenland]] and is an international co-production between Spain, France and Bulgaria.<ref name=\"Berlin\">{{cite web |url=http://www.berlinale.de/en/presse/pressemitteilungen/alle/Alle-Detail_26068.html |title=Isabel Coixet's Nobody Wants the Night to Open the 65th Berlinale |accessdate=10 January 2015 |work=Berlinale}}</ref> The film premiered with the title '''''Nobody Wants the Night'''''. Following poor reviews and sales the film was recut by Coixet and released under the title '''''Endless Night'''''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metro-films.com/films/endless_night/|title=Endless Night - Metro Films International|accessdate=8 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170108190551/http://www.metro-films.com/films/endless_night/|archive-date=8 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n[[Greenland]], 1908. [[Josephine Peary|Josephine]], the confident and bold wife of the famous Arctic explorer, [[Robert Peary]], embarks on a dangerous journey in pursuit of her husband who is seeking a route to the North Pole. She meets Allaka, an Eskimo girl who is pregnant.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Rinko Kikuchi]] as Allaka\n* [[Juliette Binoche]] as [[Josephine Diebitsch Peary|Josephine Peary]]\n* [[Gabriel Byrne]] as Bram Trevor\n* [[Matt Salinger]] as Captain Spalding\n* [[Velizar Binev]] as Fyodor\n* [[Ciro Mir\u00f3]] as Cyrus\n\n==Reception==\nThe film received negative reviews after its Berlin premiere. [[Peter Bradshaw]] from ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave the film two stars out of five and observed that \"[t]he film is possessed of blandly humanistic flavours, new-agey gestures and quaint stereotypes\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/feb/06/berlin-2015-review-nobody-wants-the-night-juliette-binoches-arctic-role-requires-more-defrosting|title=Berlin 2015 review: Nobody Wants the Night \u2013 Juliette Binoche's Arctic role requires more defrosting|author=Peter Bradshaw|work=the Guardian|accessdate=3 April 2016}}</ref> ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' called it \"inconsistent\" and \"a mixed bag\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/nobody-wants-night-berlin-review-770449|title='Nobody Wants the Night': Berlin Review|author=Boyd van Hoeij|date=5 February 2015|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=3 April 2016}}</ref> In his review for ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', Guy Lodge wrote that \"[the film] is dramatically as pallid and lifeless as the frozen tundra on which it takes place\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/festivals/berlin-film-review-isabel-coixets-nobody-wants-the-night-1201424401/|title=\u2018Nobody Wants the Night\u2019 Review: Juliette Binoche, Rinko Kikuchi Get Snowbound - Variety|author=Guy Lodge|work=Variety|accessdate=3 April 2016}}</ref> [[Indiewire]]'s Jessica Kiang criticized the script and Coixet's direction, adding that \"whenever it threatens to find its way, it soon loses it again\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/berlin-review-isabel-coixets-nobody-wants-the-night-starring-juliette-binoche-rinko-kikuchi-and-gabriel-byrne-20150205|title=Berlin Review: Isabel Coixet's 'Nobody Wants The Night' S - The Playlist|author=Jessica Kiang|date=5 February 2015|work=The Playlist|accessdate=3 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe film received a warmer reception in Coixet's native Spain after its November release, getting three and four-star reviews from outlets such as ''[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]'', ''[[Cineman\u00eda]]'' and ''[[La Vanguardia]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sensacine.com/peliculas/pelicula-218727/criticas-prensa/|title=Nadie quiere la noche: Cr\u00edticas de prensa|author=SensaCine|work=SensaCine.com|accessdate=3 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=wikitable\n! Awards !! Category !! Nominated !! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=9 | [[30th Goya Awards]]<ref name=\"Goya\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/bride-leads-goya-award-nominations-848409 |title='The Bride' Leads Spain's Goya Award Nominations |accessdate=28 December 2015 |work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref>\n| colspan=2 | Best Film\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Director\n| [[Isabel Coixet]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Actress\n| [[Juliette Binoche]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Cinematography\n| [[Jean-Claude Larrieu (cinematographer)|Jean-Claude Larrieu]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Art Direction\n| Alain Bain\u00e9e\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Production Supervision\n| Andr\u00e9s Santana and Marta Mir\u00f3\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Costume Design\n| Clara Bilbao\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Makeup and Hairstyles\n| Pablo Perona, Paco Rodr\u00edguez H. and Sylvie Imbert\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Original Score\n| [[Lucas Vidal]]\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Survival film]], about the film genre, with a list of related films\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2735996}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|endless_night_2015}}\n\n{{Isabel Coixet}}\n\n[[Category:2015 films]]\n[[Category:2010s drama films]]\n[[Category:Spanish films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian films]]\n[[Category:Spanish drama films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian drama films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Isabel Coixet]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1908]]\n[[Category:Films set in Greenland]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Lucas Vidal]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|2015 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=June 2018}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Endless Night\n| image          = Nadie quiere la noche.jpg\n| caption        = Film poster\n| director       = [[Isabel Coixet]]\n| producer       = Jaume Roures\n| writer         = [[Miguel Barros]]\n| starring       = [[Juliette Binoche]]<br>[[Rinko Kikuchi]]<br>[[Gabriel Byrne]]\n| music          = [[Lucas Vidal]]\n| cinematography = [[Jean-Claude Larrieu (cinematographer)|Jean-Claude Larrieu]]\n| editing        = Elena Ruiz \n| production companies = Mer Film<br>New Art Productions<br>Noodles Production<br>One More Movie\n| distributor    = Filmax {{small|(Spain)}}, \n| released       = {{Film date|2015|2|5|[[65th Berlin International Film Festival|Berlin]]|2015|10|30|Spain|df=yes}}\n| runtime        = 118 minutes\n| country        = Spain<br>France<br>Bulgaria\n| language       = English\n}}\n\n'''''Endless Night''''' ({{lang-es|'''Nadie quiere la noche'''}}) is a 2015 [[drama film]] directed by [[Isabel Coixet]]. It was selected to open the [[65th Berlin International Film Festival]].<ref>{{cite web | url=https://variety.com/2015/film/news/isabel-coixets-nobody-wants-the-night-to-open-berlin-film-festival-1201396594/ | title=Berlin Film Festival to Open with Juliette Binoche Starrer \u2018Nobody Wants the Night\u2019 | work=[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]] | publisher=[[Penske Media Corporation]] | date=9 January 2015 | accessdate=10 January 2015 | last=Barraclough | first=Leo}}</ref> The film is set in 1908 in [[Greenland]] and is an international co-production between Spain, France and Bulgaria.<ref name=\"Berlin\">{{cite web |url=http://www.berlinale.de/en/presse/pressemitteilungen/alle/Alle-Detail_26068.html |title=Isabel Coixet's Nobody Wants the Night to Open the 65th Berlinale |accessdate=10 January 2015 |work=Berlinale}}</ref> The film premiered with the title '''''Nobody Wants the Night'''''. Following poor reviews and sales the film was recut by Coixet and released under the title '''''Endless Night'''''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.metro-films.com/films/endless_night/|title=Endless Night - Metro Films International|accessdate=8 January 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170108190551/http://www.metro-films.com/films/endless_night/|archive-date=8 January 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\n[[Greenland]], 1908. [[Josephine Peary|Josephine]], the confident and bold wife of the famous Arctic explorer, [[Robert Peary]], embarks on a dangerous journey in pursuit of her husband who is seeking a route to the North Pole. She meets Allaka, an Eskimo girl who is pregnant.\n\n==Cast==\n* [[Rinko Kikuchi]] as Allaka\n* [[Juliette Binoche]] as [[Josephine Diebitsch Peary|Josephine Peary]]\n* [[Gabriel Byrne]] as Bram Trevor\n* [[Matt Salinger]] as Captain Spalding\n* [[Velizar Binev]] as Fyodor\n* [[Ciro Mir\u00f3]] as Cyrus\n\n==Reception==\nThe film received negative reviews after its Berlin premiere. [[Peter Bradshaw]] from ''[[The Guardian]]'' gave the film two stars out of five and observed that \"[t]he film is possessed of blandly humanistic flavours, new-agey gestures and quaint stereotypes\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.theguardian.com/film/2015/feb/06/berlin-2015-review-nobody-wants-the-night-juliette-binoches-arctic-role-requires-more-defrosting|title=Berlin 2015 review: Nobody Wants the Night \u2013 Juliette Binoche's Arctic role requires more defrosting|author=Peter Bradshaw|work=the Guardian|accessdate=3 April 2016}}</ref> ''[[The Hollywood Reporter]]'' called it \"inconsistent\" and \"a mixed bag\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/review/nobody-wants-night-berlin-review-770449|title='Nobody Wants the Night': Berlin Review|author=Boyd van Hoeij|date=5 February 2015|work=The Hollywood Reporter|accessdate=3 April 2016}}</ref> In his review for ''[[Variety (magazine)|Variety]]'', Guy Lodge wrote that \"[the film] is dramatically as pallid and lifeless as the frozen tundra on which it takes place\".<ref>{{cite web|url=https://variety.com/2015/film/festivals/berlin-film-review-isabel-coixets-nobody-wants-the-night-1201424401/|title=\u2018Nobody Wants the Night\u2019 Review: Juliette Binoche, Rinko Kikuchi Get Snowbound - Variety|author=Guy Lodge|work=Variety|accessdate=3 April 2016}}</ref> [[Indiewire]]'s Jessica Kiang criticized the script and Coixet's direction, adding that \"whenever it threatens to find its way, it soon loses it again\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://blogs.indiewire.com/theplaylist/berlin-review-isabel-coixets-nobody-wants-the-night-starring-juliette-binoche-rinko-kikuchi-and-gabriel-byrne-20150205|title=Berlin Review: Isabel Coixet's 'Nobody Wants The Night' S - The Playlist|author=Jessica Kiang|date=5 February 2015|work=The Playlist|accessdate=3 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe film received a warmer reception in Coixet's native Spain after its November release, getting three and four-star reviews from outlets such as ''[[El Mundo (Spain)|El Mundo]]'', ''[[Cineman\u00eda]]'' and ''[[La Vanguardia]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sensacine.com/peliculas/pelicula-218727/criticas-prensa/|title=Nadie quiere la noche: Cr\u00edticas de prensa|author=SensaCine|work=SensaCine.com|accessdate=3 April 2016}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\n{| class=wikitable\n! Awards !! Category !! Nominated !! Result\n|-\n| rowspan=9 | [[30th Goya Awards]]<ref name=\"Goya\">{{Cite web|url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/bride-leads-goya-award-nominations-848409 |title='The Bride' Leads Spain's Goya Award Nominations |accessdate=28 December 2015 |work=The Hollywood Reporter}}</ref>\n| colspan=2 | Best Film\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Director\n| [[Isabel Coixet]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Actress\n| [[Juliette Binoche]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Cinematography\n| [[Jean-Claude Larrieu (cinematographer)|Jean-Claude Larrieu]]\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Art Direction\n| Alain Bain\u00e9e\n| {{nom}}\n|-\n| Best Production Supervision\n| Andr\u00e9s Santana and Marta Mir\u00f3\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Costume Design\n| Clara Bilbao\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Makeup and Hairstyles\n| Pablo Perona, Paco Rodr\u00edguez H. and Sylvie Imbert\n| {{won}}\n|-\n| Best Original Score\n| [[Lucas Vidal]]\n| {{won}}\n|}\n\n==See also==\n* [[Survival film]], about the film genre, with a list of related films\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|2735996}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|endless_night_2015}}\n\n{{Isabel Coixet}}\n\n[[Category:2015 films]]\n[[Category:2010s drama films]]\n[[Category:Spanish films]]\n[[Category:French films]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian films]]\n[[Category:Spanish drama films]]\n[[Category:French drama films]]\n[[Category:Bulgarian drama films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films directed by Isabel Coixet]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1908]]\n[[Category:Films set in Greenland]]\n[[Category:Films scored by Lucas Vidal]]\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "